Moawapang:"I think India Should focus on Handling pressure in Big Games As we have stumbled way too many times In the Semis and Finals
Games like
Pak vs India 2017
Champions Trophy
Inda vs NZ in 2019
Now In 2022 AGAINST England
Yes I also I agree that India's gameplay is Old school but To be Honest it all comes down To a player handling Pressure In tough Situations And in Big Games
You have to get over your Feelings for an outcome to at least give your team a hope to Win the Game but After a wicket Less defeat against Eng in a stage like the world cup really shows How Indian Players tend to choke under pressure
And The Indian team should really focus on Handling Pressure especially on a big stage like the world cup Semi finals and Finals where so much is on stake"}

Poor selection committee"}

Ramdass S:"Nearly 14 years of IPL tournaments ..

PlugInCaroo:"India didnt do ANYTHING to upset the rythm of the Eng Batsmen ... except the wicketkeeper coming forward ... no bouncers... no team discussion... nothing... did not bowl INTO the wickets... Instead we kept bowling outside the off which if they connected went for a boundary.\r
On seaming pitches where there is early movement then it is better NOT to expose your best batsmen early on ... to send in some PINCH-HITTERS like AKSAR Patel or even the bowlers like Shami or Ashwin who can swing their bat without fear right from BALL 1. They would not have done worse than 63 from 10 overs.\r
So if we are 50 for 2 or 3 wickets in 5 overs it would not too bad with ball getting old and the best batsmen coming in... would do a lot of difference."}
